actions.message: NFA is just an alt, you can't change anything. All you can do is login to the account and play, that's it. Usually many people will have access to it.
actions.name: Add Embed Field

actions.message: SFA is a little bit better than the normal alt. It's an account with no security questions set, meaning you can change the name and the password of the account. Changing the password is a risk, as it sends the current owner of the account an email saying it's been changed although the email cannot be changed.
actions.name: Add Embed Field

actions.message: With FA accounts, you can change the email. You know the user/pass and the security questions. Which allows you to move the account onto your own email. BUT, when you change your email, it sends the old email it was associated with an email saying the minecraft account was changed, with a link to reclaim the account. Meaning, if the real owner of account is active, then you'll lose the account.
actions.name: Add Embed Field

actions.message: Basically this is the same as FA, but you have access to the email the mc account is on. So whenever you change the email, you can get on that email and delete the email to reclaim the account. The only way you can lose your account here, is if the old owner has a TID (Transaction ID).
actions.name: Add Embed Field

actions.message: You get this when the account is first bought. If anything ever happens to your account, you can just contact mojang with this, and you'll get your account back. Doesn't work all the time. Usually these are sold with a FA or EA account, making it more secure.
actions.name: Add Embed Field

actions.message: A NFA account with an optifine cape on it. You can visit optifine's site and move the cape to your own account.
actions.name: Add Embed Field

actions.message: The best and most secure account in my opinion. An account that has not yet been migrated. When buying these, make sure the seller is selling the user/pass/email. When you migrate it to your email, you'll have EA, with no chance of it gettid TID'd back. These are the best accounts to snipe names on.
